# Motion-Detection Masks

## Never auto-resize masks to fit frames

Motion masks define pixel-accurate monitoring regions. Silently resizing a mask to match frame dimensions corrupts the intended geometry and produces incorrect detection results.

If the mask dimensions do not match the frame dimensions, **abort with a clear error** telling the user the exact sizes so they can regenerate the mask at the correct resolution.

## Mask generation

Masks must be created at the exact resolution that frames will have after any ffmpeg scaling (e.g. `scale=WIDTH:-2`). The `-2` flag rounds height to even, so the mask height must account for this. When in doubt, extract a single frame at the target width first and use its dimensions for the mask.
